description: In 1938 New York City, when the country is at the brink of war, Tony Stark has discovered something that could turn the tide…and save his life. The plot thickens as Tony and his crew take to the high seas in search of the Lost City of Atlantis, with the Nazis hot on their heels. Scott Snyder and Manuel Garcia reimagine classic Marvel characters as they’ve never been seen before, in the second issue of a pulp thrill ride you won’t want to miss!

If you can't trust a semi-autonomous battle cruiser from space to betray you to a bunch of alien gods, who CAN you trust? That's the question facing the mutant tyrant Apocalypse when Ship, the Celestial artifact-turned-X-Factor-HQ, develops sentience and starts reporting to its makers. What exactly has Ship told the omnipotent Celestials...and what does it all have to do with young Christopher Summers?
name: Unexpected Host

description: It's a reprint from the first Fantastic Four Annual.
name: Fantastic Four Special Edition
Sign of the Vampire Cat
Project Doomsday
Survival!

description:
It didn’t matter very much what you gave Ken Bradley, boxer turned paratrooper, to fight with. His bare fists made him a match for a handful of Germans any day.
But give him a gun, especially a Tommy gun, and he’d take on anything that had a swastika painted on it. Even a tank…or a pill-box! What a man to have a your side.

Originally Commando No 252
name: Battling Bradley
Under Two Flags
Redcap Rat
The Crown of Marcellus
One Mans War

description: An all-new, exclusive story officially set in the world of the IRON MAN movies! Co-written by IRON MAN 2 screenwriter Justin Theroux and IRON MAN: ENTER THE MANDARIN writer Joe Casey, with art by Barry Kitson (AMAZING SPIDER-MAN)! Find out HERE how Tony Stark gets from point A – the “I am Iron Man” press conference from the blockbuster hit IRON MAN – to point B when the story of IRON MAN 2 begins and Tony is butting heads with the U.S. government. Everybody wants to get their hands on Tony Stark’s game-changing Iron Man technology…and Tony knows the damage his armor could wreak in irresponsible hands. But a reckless military leader gets involved – a familiar Marvel face with close ties to Tony’s past – and he’s got his own plans that don’t involve waiting for Stark to just hand over the suit…
name: Public Identity (Part 3)

description:
Hunted as imposters and suspected in Toa Lhikan's disappearance, the Toa Metru are forced to flee for their lives. Stowing away aboard a Le-Metru airship, they mistakenly believe themselves to be beyond the reach of the Vahki order enforcement squads.  
Meanwhile, a far more dangerous threat is looming in the shape of Nidhiki and Krekka, the Dark Hunters. Dispatched by Turaga Dume to capture the outlaws, they are determined to bring the Toa in alive - if not necessarily undamaged. 
For the Toa, capture would mean both Lhikan and the city itself would be lost forever. But can they hope to survive against beings who live to hunt Toa?
name: Struggle in the Sky

description:
Having found a new land where they hope the Matoran will be safe from harm, the Toa Metra have returned to Metru Nui to save the rest of the population. But they have come back to a city radically changed, and for the worse - darkness and strange webs shroud the buildings, and earthquake has badly damaged large areas, and bizarre creatures are visible moving through the mist. Worse, the Archives have been shattered, freeing every Rahi inside to roam the city. 
Despite all this, Toa Vakama remains confident that his team can rescue the sleeping Matoran from beneath the Coliseum and get them out of the city. After all, they are Toa! They have defeated Makuta, Dark Hunters, Vahki, and the Morbuzakh. There is nothing in this city of shadows that could harm them... 
Or is there?
name: Monsters in the Dark

description: The Toxic Avenger encounters his mother for the first time after his transformation. Meanwhile mutants attack the high school.
name: Apocalypse inc.
Letal Linda And The Legend Of Sludgeface

description: The police mistake the Toxic Avenger for Sludgeface and open fire.
name: Dr. Chemo's Biohazard (or: A Myth Of Modern Pollution)
The Stirring Saga Of Biohazard - Part II: Not Fit For Fertilizer

description: The Chairman of Apocalypse Inc. has unleashed poisoned, mutation-causing Souvlaki upon New York City.
name: The Souvlaki Sewer Syndrome (Part 1): Sinister Slinkers

description:
Mender, Krim, Drub, Flam and Shuna witness Zhantee die in Cutter's arms, whose spirit is immediately received into family of The High-Ones.

Aroree leaves the rest of the wolfriders in order to find and deliver Skywise and Timmain to the SHARDs.

Meanwhile, Venka Winnowill, and a knocked-out Rayek are in the SHARDroom, and the Grohmul Djun is enraged at his half-human-elf lover's deceit. The moment the Zhantee enters oneness with The High-Ones, he delivers a force-shield that prevents a deathblow from the human ruler. Her righteousness helped Zhantee to "send"share his gift, and Kahvi blocks his attempts to kill both Rayek and Winnowill.

elfQuest SHARDS #12, October '95
name: The Key

description:
SHARDS #13, "Underground" shows Cutter's band, with Shuna the leader of the rebellion against the Djun, though Two-Edge's master work. He has built a maze with many dangers, snares, spoils, a few traps, and also some spike awaiting the subteranean travellers.

Strongbow almost falls into a pit, when Two-Edge's spine-like bridge gives out. He firest an arrow with rope-attachment, hoping that it can catch on in desperation. And it hits through Shuna's hand, meanwhile Drub & Flam, commonly regarded as a duo, pull him to the safety of their ledge.

The whole issue is dedicated to the warrior's journey through Two-Edge's twisted cavern. Finally, the troupe is knocking on the SHARD-Palace's gate. So Cutter & Strongbow decide to hold the kitchen-staff hostage while the elves and #Trolls have a big meal.

In this issue, the gift of the healers, especially Mender and Leetah, is proclaimed to be the greatest help in the arsenal of war-tactics. This is the same gift that Winnowill usee to hurt.
name: Underground

first_appearance_teams.name: Humans of the World of Two Moons

team_credits.name: Humans of the World of Two Moons

description:
Series interchange

elfQuest SHARDS is WaRP graphics dual offering during a time when Ember was chieftain and Cutter was her field-general. Skywise has his first reappearance after being part of Ember's Quest in another series.

Reinforcements

SHARDS is a series that ran parallel with another elfQuest series, called

Cutter, Treestump, Clearbrook, Mender, Krim, and Strongbow, have finally entered the Crystalline-array of the SHARDS, fragments once the Palace of the High Ones. The forces of remembrance renew the elves family Spirit.

Finally, the Grohmul Djun has been captured and imprisoned with the Preserver's wrapstuff.

The Djun's Citadel catches on fire when a tray of candles spills nearby some curtains. Shuna, with one fighting hand, is left at the end of SHARDS#14 with a chance to behead the Djun with his sword.
name: Reunion

description:
This issue is available to read online in the elfQuest archive, at http://www.elfQuest.com .

The SHARDS Unite

With the Scrol of Colours set in place, Suntop, Timmain, and Skywise call forth the power of each SHARD fragment, and the pieces create an egg-cocoon for everyone to travel. Shuna, and Two-Edge join the elves for a wild, cosmic voyage.

Shortly after the shards unite and form an aircraft/spaceship, the elves decide to travel everywhere on their planet, and collect every last elf, from Savah and the Sun Villagers, to Ember, Teir and the Wolfriders. Ember has hard-news telling Mender about her new lover. Even the Go-Backs find their way into the Egg-Palace. They ask Venka to be their next Chief.

Finally, all of the elves are together. Ember has demonstrated her authority. Now all the elftribes can go on a cosmic voyage and explore everywhere that Skywise has long sinced dreamed of. Right?

Wrong: Cutter will remain with the planet. Rayek goes off with the egg-palace-shard until it launches he and Timmain on a glorious and astounding cosmic voyage, also with the rest of The High-Ones.

By now, the elves are not only celebrated by the medeivel townsfolk of "The World of Two-Moons" but have dominance over Picknoses Trolls. Did I mention that Drub & Flam return to their caverns, with lots and lots of human trinkets and treasures. Yes.

By the end of this series, the power of the High Ones and all the elves who have died is reunited into one single family bond, that includes every elf known to readers up to this point in nineteen 96.

Rayek becomes human prison

Instead of going on a glorious space voyage with Skywise and Timmain, Rayek has inherited all of the dark inclinations from his lover. Now, he is destined to go on an independent final Quest, in Rogues Curse, published within ElfQuest Volume 2 (33 Issues).

Note: In addition to Wendy & Richard Pini, this comic was produced by Mary Lou Keenan and Peggy Snow, and delivered to customers by Daniel Pilkington.

Note on EQ SHARDS #16, March '96: This particular issue is not a panelled comic strip. Its format, unlike EQ#15, is told in a children's book formate. The usual script was all capital-lettering, but this conclusion is featured in lower-cased COURIER font.
name: The New Beginning...

deck: A collaboration between Warp and BMP.
description: The sea-elves celebrate the crowning festival. A storyteller says their ancestors arrived from the sky and met with death from humans. Five fled with an injured preserver. Ausra was lost to the river. The survivors were trapped on the cliffs by a giant maraeva. They jumped into the ocean. Ausra saved them, riding a whale. The Bay of Solitude was their new home. Ausra, the first crown, Livian, Sima, and Desh chose to become like dolphins. The Wavedancers were born. The festival lasts two months. Sleia finds Barmek outside. He feels he should be somewhere else. They swim up the Shoaltail River. Korilla (with octopus arms below the waist) prepares the feast. Cubs Inkbottom and Shoresprout go to Tentus's cave, guardian of knowledge, firstborn, and hermit. They go through the Chamber of Remembrance to his sleep chamber. He says to get Rhialdor. Barmek and Sleia sit and talk. When he was a squirt his mother would disappear. He followed her into a hidden tunnel and found a long-kept secret. Because of him, Brom sent Raenafel away. Sleia says she's back now. She passed all the tests. She's not the same elf Barmek saw then. He wants to search for the true crown. They head off into the night. He can't believe his brother Jormak's behavior. They got an open sending yesterday. Hyfus led them since Brom's death. Jormak said the children of Recognition were taken from them by an unknown power. Brom's daughter was one. She was sent to escape and bring a High One. Jormak's mother had a dream and told him to set forth and bring home two travelers. He returned with a High One, Sydor, and Raenafel. She's actually Winnowill.
name: Search for the True Crown, Part One

person_credits.name: Josef Szekeres
person_credits.role: writer, artist, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

deck: A collaboration between Warp and BMP.
description: Barmek and Sleia are in the forest at night. Barmek can't keep silent. Raenafel is an imposter. The preserver No-Wing seems to have disappeared. Sydor said it was in the Palace with its own kind. "Raenafel" went before the one who birthed her, her teacher and protector, Kirith, who is now blind. Raenafel asks her to think back. She does and agrees it's truly her. Barmek thinks her blindness should have been a surprise. The Wavedancers are feasting. Raenafel senses trouble between Hyfus and Tilaweed. Jormak says they haven't been right since the loss of their child of Recognition. They wonder about Barmek and Sleia. Rhialdor brings in the next dish. Tentus wants Raenafel and Sydor to visit. They are led to his chamber. He felt sickness when a child of Recognition was about to be taken. He feels it now. The next day, a bear chases Barmek. Sleia pulls him up to a branch. They eat dreamberries and get drunk. Sleia starts hallucinating. Kirith sends to all the Wavedancers. They all come, even Raenafel and Sydor. They need to search. Rhialdor asks Raenafel to restore his lifemate's sight. It began with a dream. She gave birth to twins. Two spiders crawled out and attacked her eyes. She awoke blind. She knew to send Jormak for them. She was given the gift of foresight. Barmek and Sleia attack a bear while still drunk. Barmek holds his knife up as it runs, killing it. They travel the rest of the day and then rest. A large group of ants surround them.
name: Search for the True Crown, Part Two

person_credits.name: Josef Szekeres
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

deck: A collaboration between Warp and BMP.
description: Sydor and "Raenafel" are in their chamber. Sydor says the missing ones must be found. Jormak enters. There is no sign of Barmek and Sleia. The others want to know why they have this curse. They ask Sydor for help but he has no answers for them. He and Raenafel leave. They must think faster. He starts ranting, angering Winnowill. He sends, unleashing her despair, her searing memories. Suddenly he's confused. He collapses, revealing his instability. He decides he must take control. The tribe shares their grief with Hyfus. He's noticed Tilaweed is so cold about it. She's off watching the sun set, crying. Barmek and Sleia are many leagues inland, swimming up the Shoaltail. Soon they come to the ruins of Blue Mountain, silent testimony to failed ambition. They find pieces of the Great Egg and remains of giant birds. Sleia is bitten by a snake. The numbness begins to spread. Barmek carries her to the forest. At night she falls unconscious. A deer comes to him, then runs off. Water drips on Sleia's face, waking her up. He starts bringing more water. Over a few days she regains her strength and they can continue. After more days pass they can see the frozen mountains to the north. Sleia becomes delusional, thinking Barmek wants to kill her. She attacks him and he fights back. She pushes him off a cliff and runs into the night screaming, "Freedom!" She runs until she collapses. She awakes to No-Wing spitting wrapstuff. It takes her to a bundle in a cliff face.
name: Search for the True Crown, Part Three

deck: A collaboration between Warp and BMP.
description: Brom and Kirith help his lifemate Ailsa give birth. There's so much pain and birth-blood. It's the curse that threatens to obliterate any child born of Recognition. The Wavedancers mourn, knowing that the child will be taken. Kirith takes the child up for her first breath. She returns and Ailsa is dead. She's to tell the others the child is also dead. He performs the death ritual and returns Ailsa to the sea. He takes Raenafel to a hidden cave, where she grows up with the help of Brom, Kirith, and No-Wing. She's taught about Recognition and soul names. One day Barmek follows his mother and discovers the secret. Raenafel gets his soul name and it is with her always. Raenafel must go into hiding. Brom tells the truth to the tribe. Raenafel will go to the Palace and return with a High One. The present: Sleia suddenly remembers Barmek and finds him at the bottom of the cliff. She carries him back. No-Wing says Raenafel has healing power. She carries Raenafel into the water and unwraps her. She brings Barmek, also wrapped, into the water and frees him. Raenafel rises out of the water. Barmek blacks out. The knowing part of him, his dreamspeak, takes him back to when choices were clear. Raenafel comes to him. He was too young when they Recognized. Not now. They become a buck and a doe and run off. He wakes up. They tell Raenafel about Winnowill, about Kirith's blindness, and about how her father, Brom, died fighting the curse. They don't head for the Palace, No-Wing said it blinked away (Kings of the Broken Wheel). They head home.
name: Search for the True Crown, Part Four

deck: A collaboration between Warp and BMP.
description: Jormak joins with Winnowill. He gives her his soul name. It's two days before crowning. She says the Palace is a place of blue rocks that shifts into the shape of an egg. They'll leave the world behind while the others sleep eternally. In the Chamber of Remembrance Sydor tells them the Palace is a crystal sphere stained with the blood of the High Ones. It's not how No-Wing described it. All the worlds they went to spoiled High Ones' magic. First children of Recognition were taken, then Brom, and now Barmek and Sleia. Korillia's mother passed through a whirlpool of old magic and her octopus legs were the result. Before, she was happy, but she discovered she's barren. They'll travel among the stars, reunited with spirits of loved ones. Sydor calls to Winnowill. She knows he can't control her. Since Tyldak dropped her on his island he waited patiently as she healed. If he's betrayed she'll pay. Shoresprout wouldn't believe that Inkbottom's sister is Sleia. His father tells him they're both right, she's his half-sister. He goes to tell her but Sydor draws him away. Elsewhere, Sleia tells Raenafel that she and Barmek will be lifemates, they've been together since they were squirts. Raenafel sees a piece of the egg in her hand and says they must go, now. She and Barmek are fighting Recognition sickness. Morning, the eve of the crowning: Rhialdor asks his son Jormak to talk to his mother Kirith. She isn't taking Barmek's loss well. He says she should get over it and walks away. At night they all gather for a sea hunt. Tomorrow Hyfus will hand his duties to "Raenafel," his final duty. She wants Jormak to do it, breaking tradition. She and Sydor will leave them behind, even Jormak. Winnowill rests for the ceremony.
name: Search for the True Crown, Part Five

deck: A collaboration between Warp and BMP.
description: The sea hunt begins. Sydor is disgusted by them. Inkbottom and Shoresprout catch a large fish. The travelers are homeward bound as a storm approaches. Barmek tells Raenafel that their union would be doomed. At home, only the most succulent catches are kept. Tilaweed remains silent. Inkbottom and Shoresprout are with Tentus in the Chamber of Remembrance. Ausra shaped some who chose to swim like fish. She went away because she couldn't stop the curse of Recognition. Barmek, Sleia, and Raenafel take cover from the storm. When the moons rise the crowning will begin. The storytellers begin. Ausra gives courage to the new ruler, Neama gives compassion, Brom gives determination. Winnowill enters as Barmek, Sleia, and Raenafel arrive. They've come to stop it. Jormak says it's treachery. He attacks Barmek, knocking him unconscious. The true Raenafel heals Kirith's eyes. Kirith yells, "Stop!" She now knows who the true Raenafel is. Sydor acts confused. Raenafel throws her ceremonial trident, cutting his face. She's seen what he's forgotten. She pulls away the curtains in his mind. He is reminded of how the humans welcomed the High Ones with death. He collapses to the floor. The Wavedancers disgust Winnowill, there's no fight in them. She's tired of their foolishness. She sends, knocking them to the floor. Raenafel punches her and is slammed into a wall. As Winnowill leaves, Jormak follows. Barmek can no longer fight it and goes off with Raenafel. Winnowill leaves Jormak as Barmek and Raenafel finally answer Recognition's call.
name: Search for the True Crown, Part Six

description: There are worlds beyond our own. There are powers we don’t understand. And there are pets that cannot be controlled. Are the Pet Avengers might enough to save the entire world from amazing creatures of myth?

volume.name: Lockjaw and the Pet Avengers Unleashed

description: WAR OF THE IRON MEN! Tony Stark wages a one-man invasion of Transia to hunt down and destroy the renegade Iron Men, setting off an international conflagration that threatens to engulf his friends, his company, and everything he's worked for! All this sets the stage for a jaw-dropping, no-holds-barred, heavy-metal armored slugfest the likes of which you've never seen! When the mysterious source behind the Iron Men is revealed on the last page, you won't believe your eyes…and neither will Tony!
name: War of the Iron Men, Part Two

description: Marvel's Greatest Comics $1.00
name: The Golden History

description: A map found in the bottom of a crypt has led Dane and Maya deep inside a series of caverns filled with chugawug outlaws and deadly traps. Then, just when it looks like their luck is about to turn, Maya flies into danger and it's up to Dane and a monstrous friend to get her out.
name: Like A Bird In A Cage

description: Based on the new hit series from Warner Bros. TV on Fox! Christopher Chance might have finally undertaken a job even he can't complete – protecting a client against every organized crime family in Europe!
name: The Wanted: Extremely DEAD Contract!, Clause Four: Alpine Panic!

description: It's Magog versus The Shield when Killer App takes hold! But why are the Planeteers keeping their distance from Magog as well?
name: In Too Deep

description: "Operation: Gunslinger" continues as The Shield teams up with the Justice Society of America for an adventure in the sleepy town of Happy Harbor! Plus, The Fox is now a fully trained martial arts master, but is he ready to face the deadly Dragon's Head clan?
name: Operation: Gunslinger; The Fox, Part 3

description:
A Cold War Heats Up!

Finn and Glori, the bearers of the Glacier and Ember Stones, have discovered that a mysterious cult is after Pandora’s Box, one of the 13 Artifacts. Will they be able to not kill each other long enough to prevent the Disciples of Eden from destroying the world? Or will they revert to their destined roles?
name: Part 2

description: Coyle and Avery discover just how far the virus has spread when they escape up the Oregon coast. As they encounter other survivors and learn more about the infection, they begin to understand exactly what it will take to stay safe from THE LIGHT.

During the Great War on Cybertron, one of the Autobots’ fallen heroes was Optimus Prime's best friend—IRONHIDE. What does that have to do with the fate of the planet today? Find out in this all-new miniseries by TRANSFORMERS writer Mike Costa and the phenomenal Casey Coller. You didn't really think his death was just some stunt with no ramifications, did you?

The story begins 4 million years ago on Cybertron. The Autobots are battling the Decepticons. In the battle, Optimus heads off to flank the Decepticons to keep them from delivering a shipment of energon. On the way, he is ambushed by Soundwave and Rumble but Ironhide comes to his aid. Optimus then ambushes the Decepticons with the energon shipment and with Ironhide's help, he manages to apprehend them by threatening to blow up the shipment even if it destroys 4 city blocks. Later, the Autobots are celebrating their victory and Optimus is praised for bringing the 5 Decepticons in without any fighting and he says it's because he has good Autobots with him. Prowl asks Optimus if he's going to give them a speech and he declines saying that it's a night for the Autobots to relax and let off some steam. Kup insists Prime talk to them, but Prime says he's a soldier and isn't that good with words - especially since he'd had too many at Maccadam's. Ironhide agrees with Optimus saying that there's no reason to mess with a party when they already know how good Optimus is at taking down Decepticons. Kup still insists he does saying that he's a Prime and he has to start seeing things past the tactical. Prime says he does see them and he also believes that the war is going to last a very long time because what they're fighting is a philosophy - an idea and so it can't be beaten. Ironhide asks if he means they can't win and Prime responds by saying that an idea can't be defeated but it can be changed but he doesn't know what it takes to do that yet and until he or someone else figures out how to they're just going to have to keep winning battles. As they go back to the party, Ironhide says that Prime is the finest soldier he's ever seen and he loves him but doesn't understand him. Kup sympathizes with Ironhide. As Ironhide joins back in the party, he notices a certain Autobot and asks Silverstreak if he's seen him before. Silverstreak replies saying he has but doesn't remember his name. Ironhide has a bad feeling about him but Silverstreak, like most other Autobots, is drunk out of his mind and isn't really concerned. Ironhide however, realizes that he's looking at Prime's back and sees he's about to grab his gun and then the mysterious bot yells, "Death to Autobots!" and fires at Prime, but Ironhide manages to get in the way and takes the blast for him. Then in the modern day, Ironhide then wakes up in shock and finds himself in a dark room and starts thanking the Autobots for patching him up but doesn't find anyone else there with him. As he continues to search, he realizes that he's on Cybertron alone...
name: The Iron Age

description: The all-new, all-ages, all-action fun continues! It's wall-to-wall mayhem in the Mighty Marvel Manner with four original tales of everybody's favorite teenage wall-crawler! Featuring the X-MEN and BULLSEYE! Collecting MARVEL ADVENTURES SPIDER-MAN #58-61.
name: Peter Parker Vs. The X-Men

volume.name: Marvel Adventures Spider-Man: Peter Parker Vs. The X-Men

description: The Historic binding of Al'Lan Mandragoran as Warder to Moiraine of the Aes Sedai is upon us and the search ensues for the Dragon Reborn, so that he may be saved to fulfill his destiny and oppose the Dark One in an ultimate Last Battle. However, followers of the Dark One also know the prophecy and a desperate race ensues with the fate of all mankind hanging in the balance. The Adventure has just begun!

volume.name: Robert Jordan's The Wheel of Time: New Spring

description: As a Tek virus rampages through the sector and violently alters the programming of the meks, androids and every other automated system, Jake Cardigan races to find the source before society implodes. However, what he finds can change his life forever. Based on the best-selling Tek novels by entertainment icon William Shatner this second issue of Volume 2 answers questions raised in the Volume I and unveils even more surprises.
name: Persistence of Memory Chapter 2: Rain Rain Go Away

volume.name: William Shatner Presents: The Tek War Chronicles

description: The Wheel of Time turns and Ages come and go, leaving memories that become legend. Legend fades to myth, and even myth is long forgotten when the Age that gave it birth returns again. In the Third Age, an Age of Prophecy, the World and Time themselves hang in the balance. What was, what will be, and what is, may yet fall under the Shadow. Strangers have come to the village of Emond's Field, located in Two Rivers, during the Bel Tine holiday. With theses strangers come stories of the outside world: tales of war and of a man who claims to be the Dragon Reborn, the one prophesized to save the world, and also to destroy it in his madness. For it is known that no man can channel the One Power without going horribly insane. Featuring issues 0 and 1 of the series, from writer Robert Jordan – joined by the legendary Chuck Dixon – along with artist Chase Conley! 64 BIG pages with bonus materials!
name: Raven

volume.name: Robert Jordan's Wheel of Time: The Eye of the World

description: Strangers, a Gleeman, a peddler from afar and even fireworks might possibly make this the best Bel Tine ever in Two Rivers. Well, if it wasn't for the bestial Trollocs and fearsome Myrddraal waiting to attack Two Rivers in search of the Dragon Reborn... Moiraine Damodred, an Aes Sedai, and her Warder, al'Lan Mandragoran, are all that stand in the way of the Darkness that has descended on Two Rivers. And Rand al'Thor and his two friends, Matrim Cauthon and Perrin Aybara, must leave the only home they have ever known if they want to spare their loved ones from any further danger.

volume.name: Robert Jordan's Wheel of Time: The Eye of the World

description: The Skrulls are coming for Asgard, and they've got the gods in their sights! But it's not just the pantheon who stand to suffer the repercussions of the aliens' secret invasion -- the citizens of small-town Broxton, Oklahoma are about to become collateral damage in the attack, and the God of Thunder must defend two cites at once! For a job this big, Thor will have to turn to one of his oldest and closest allies: Beta Ray Bill! Collecting SECRET INVASION: THOR #1-3 and THOR #142.
name: TPB
